Instead of: Separate marker components
rust
struct EntityFlags: u32 {
const IS_PLAYER = 1 << 0;
const IS_ENEMY = 1 << 1;
const CAN_BE_DAMAGED = 1 << 2;
const IS_VISIBLE = 1 << 3;
}

ul.li:
Sparse Sets: Rare components (Dialogue, QuestMarker, DebugTag)
Rare components don't fragment archetypes;
they exist in parallel sparse set storage

div.p:
Diagnostic Metrics:
rust
fn archetype_health_check(world: &World) {
let count = world.archetype_count();
let entities = world.entity_count();
let ratio = entities as f32 / count as f32;
if ratio < 10.0 {
warn!("Archetype fragmentation! Avg {} entities/archetype", ratio);
}
}
